About 1 percent of the population goes through at least once in their life with schizophrenia; in psychiatric clinics it is treated with a frequency only second to depression.
In an acute schizophrenic psychosis, people who are affected are overexcited, which can result in hallucinations, megalomania, paranoia or persecution mania.
