The asphalt of the highways we crossed with the Boxster Spyder was fairly beaten, but the car handled the potholes well.
The electronic aids rarely showed up on the course, because, well into the morning, we found early morning ice and gravel on some curves.
In short, it is an ultra lightweight car, one of the most fun to drive on the market, and is a bit more than a simple modification of the Boxster S.
